This paper focuses on addressing the storage overhead issue in document database systems, which is a common problem in the field of database management (cs.DB). The proposed solution involves using Log Structured Merge (LSM) trees, which are commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR) systems. The paper also discusses the impact on query performance, which is a concern in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
